                  </hi>. On the night of 29th Aug., about 9 o'clock, or a little after, I was walking along Houndsditch, and felt a tug at my coat pocket,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185209200053"></xptr>
               <p>where my handkerchief was—I turned round, and saw the prisoner crossing the street—I took hold of his collar, and said, "What have you been doing?"—at the same time a witness, who is here, exclaimed, "He has thrown your handkerchief down;" I saw him pick it up, and he gave it to me—this is it (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—it is mine.</p>
